msgid ""
"If :guilabel:`Included in Price` is enabled, subsequent taxes "
"with :guilabel:`Base affected by preceding taxes` will be based on a "
"modified sales price equal to the original sales price minus the tax amount."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:420
msgid ""
"A product has a sales price of $1100, and we apply a "
"10% :guilabel:`Percentage of Price` tax with :guilabel:`Included in Price` "
"and :guilabel:`Affect base of subsequent taxes`. Any subsequent tax "
"with :guilabel:`Base affected by preceding taxes` will be based on a "
"modified sales price of $1000."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:425
msgid ""
"This setting is considered any time multiple taxes are applied to the same "
"product line, whether via a :ref:`group of taxes <taxes/computation>` or "
"multiple taxes added directly to a product line."
msgstr ""
"Ce paramètre est pris en compte chaque fois que plusieurs taxes sont "
"appliquées à la même ligne de produit, que ce soit via un :ref:`groupe de "
"taxes <taxes/computation>` ou plusieurs taxes ajoutées directement à une "
"ligne de produit."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:None
msgid "The eco-tax is taken into the basis of the 21% VAT tax"
msgstr "L'écotaxe est prise en compte dans la base de la TVA de 21%"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:432
msgid ""
"The order in which you add the taxes on a product line has no effect on how "
"amounts are computed. If you add taxes directly on a product line, only the "
"tax sequence determines the order in which they are applied."
msgstr ""
"L'ordre dans lequel vous ajoutez les taxes sur une ligne de produit n'a "
"aucun effet sur la façon dont les montants sont calculés. Si vous ajoutez "
"les taxes directement sur une ligne de produit, seule la séquence des taxes "
"détermine l'ordre dans lequel elles sont appliquées."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:436
msgid ""
"To reorder the sequence, go to :menuselection:`Accounting --> Configuration "
"--> Taxes`, and drag and drop the lines with the handles next to the tax "
"names."
msgstr ""
"Pour réorganiser la séquence, allez à :menuselection:`Comptabilité --> "
"Configuration --> Taxes`, et faites glisser et déposer les lignes avec les "
"indicateurs situés à côté des noms de taxes."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:0
msgid "The taxes' sequence in Odoo determines which tax is applied first"
msgstr ""
"La séquence des taxes dans Odoo détermine quelle taxe s'applique en premier"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:445
msgid "Base affected by preceding taxes"
msgstr "Base affected by preceding taxes"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:447
msgid ""
"This setting, which is only visible in :doc:`developer mode <../../general/"
"developer_mode>`, determines whether any previous tax that :ref:`affects the "
"base of subsequent taxes <taxes/base-subsequent>` will modify the sales "
"price that this tax is based on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:452
msgid ""
"Taxes with :ref:`Included in Price <taxes/included-in-price>` always behave "
"as if this setting is enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:456
msgid "Extra taxes"
msgstr "Taxes supplémentaires"

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:458
msgid ""
"\"Extra taxes\" is a broad term referring to additional taxes beyond the "
"standard or basic taxes imposed by governments. These extra taxes can be "
"**luxury** taxes, **environmental** taxes, **import** or **export duties** "
"taxes, etc."
msgstr ""
"Les « taxes supplémentaires » sont un terme général désignant des taxes "
"additionnelles au-delà des taxes standard ou de base imposées par les "
"gouvernements. Ces taxes supplémentaires peuvent être des taxes de **luxe**, "
"des taxes **environnementales**, des taxes de **droits d'importation** ou "
"**d'exportation**, etc."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:463
msgid ""
"The method to compute these taxes varies across different countries. We "
"recommend consulting your country's regulations to understand how to "
"calculate them for your business."
msgstr ""
"La méthode de calcul de ces taxes varie selon les pays. Nous recommandons de "
"consulter la réglementation de votre pays pour comprendre comment les "
"calculer pour votre entreprise."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:466
msgid ""
"To compute an extra tax in Odoo, :ref:`create a tax <taxes/configuration>`, "
"enter a tax name, select a :ref:`Tax Computation <taxes/configuration>`, set "
"an :guilabel:`Amount`, and in the :guilabel:`Advanced Options` tab, "
"enable :guilabel:`Affect Base of Subsequent Taxes`. Then, drag and drop the "
"taxes in the :ref:`order they should be computed <taxes/base-subsequent>`."
msgstr ""
"Pour calculer une taxe supplémentaire dans Odoo, :ref:`créer une taxe <taxes/"
"configuration>`, saisir un nom de taxe, sélectionner un :ref:`calcul de taxe "
"<taxes/configuration>`, définir un :guilabel:`montant`, et dans l'onglet "
":guilabel:`options avancées`, activer :guilabel:`affecte la base des taxes "
"suivantes`. Ensuite, glisser-déposer les taxes dans l':ref:`ordre dans "
"lequel elles doivent être calculées <taxes/base-subsequent>`."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:472
msgid ""
"In Belgium, the formula to compute an environmental tax is: `(product price "
"+ environmental tax) x sales tax`. Therefore, our environmental tax has to "
"come *before* the sales tax in the computation sequence."
msgstr ""
"En Belgique, la formule pour calculer une taxe environnementale est : `(prix "
"du produit + taxe environnementale) x taxe de vente`. Par conséquent, notre "
"taxe environnementale doit venir *avant* la taxe de vente dans la séquence "
"de calcul."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:475
msgid ""
"In our case, we created a 5% environmental tax (Ecotax) and put it *before* "
"the Belgian base tax of 21%."
msgstr ""
"Dans notre cas, nous avons créé une taxe environnementale de 5 % (Ecotax) et "
"l'avons placée *avant* la taxe de base belge de 21 %."

#: ../../content/applications/finance/accounting/taxes.rst:0
msgid "Environmental tax sequence in Belgium."
msgstr "Séquence de la taxe environnementale en Belgique."

